Es gibt kein richtiges Leben im Falschen\rquote  (GS 4 p.43)].}{\cs17\f40\fs20\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn {\footnote\ftnalt \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs17\f40\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn }{\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  Literally translated this means: \lquote There is no correct living in the False\rquote  where 
\lquote the False\rquote  is a deliberate inversion of \lquote the True\rquote  in Hegel\rquote s famous dictum from the Preface to the }{\i\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 Ph\'e4nomenologie des Geistes}{\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 , 
\lquote Das Wahre is das Ganze.\rquote  Hegel 1986: 24. As always, though, the most literal translation would be ugly and unhelpful.}}}{\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 
By this thesis Adorno means above all that in a false world there is no way of doing (and no way of knowing we are doing) the morally or politically right thing. Rational subjects cannot be sure that even apparently harmless or valuable activ
ities are not contributing covertly and in spite of their intentions to the general state of alienation and unfreedom that pervades modern (mid-twentieth Century) society. Second, it means that there is no real }{
\i\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 living }{\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 in a false life.}{\cs17\f40\fs20\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn {\footnote\ftnalt \pard\plain 
\s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs17\f40\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn }{\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  Geuss 1999: 103.}}}{
\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  There are just vario
us modes of surviving. Adorno thinks that as a result of the gradual spread of administrative systems and processes of commodification the social world has been systematically denuded of intrinsically valuable or worthwhile ends. Everything in the social 
world has come to exist for the sake of something else. This is the state of affairs that Adorno calls \lquote universal fungibility\rquote . (PDM 228) What appear to be ends in themselves \endash 
 say cultural activities and intellectual pursuits - have been annexed by all-per
vasive forms of economy and administration and turned into mere means for the attainment of self-preservation. In sum, Adorno holds that in the modern, late-capitalist world nothing is good in itself save the end of self-preservation, and whatever is valu
able is only instrumentally valuable for the control of nature and for self-preservation. (DA 9-48) Finally, we should note the implication of this thesis that, properly speaking, }{\i\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 life}{
\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  is more than mere survival; it is living well or flourishing.}{\cs17\f40\fs20\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn {\footnote\ftnalt \pard\plain 
\s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs17\f40\super\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 \chftn }{\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903  See Adorno\rquote 
s motto to }{\i\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 Minima Moralia }{\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 by Ferdinand K\'fcrnberger \lquote Life does not live\rquote  [}{\i\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 Das leben lebt nicht}{
\f40\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 ] MM 19.}}}{\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903   
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f40\fs20\insrsid13633421\charrsid10958903 
